#: ../../../statements.rst:4
msgid "Statements"
msgstr "陳述句"

#: ../../../statements.rst:6
msgid ""
"Vyper's statements are syntactically similar to Python, with some notable "
"exceptions."
msgstr "Vyper 的陳述句在語法上與 Python 相似，但有一些顯著的例外。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:9
msgid "Control Flow"
msgstr "控制流程"

#: ../../../statements.rst:12
msgid "break"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../statements.rst:14
msgid "The ``break`` statement terminates the nearest enclosing ``for`` loop."
msgstr "``break`` 陳述句會終止最近的封閉 ``for`` 迴圈。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:16
msgid ""
"for i: uint256 in [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]:\n"
"    if i == a:\n"
"        break"
msgstr ""
"for i: uint256 in [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]:\n"
"    if i == a:\n"
"        break"

#: ../../../statements.rst:22
msgid "In the above example, the ``for`` loop terminates if ``i == a``."
msgstr "在上面的範例中，如果 ``i == a``，``for`` 迴圈會終止。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:25
msgid "continue"
msgstr "continue"

#: ../../../statements.rst:27
msgid ""
"The ``continue`` statement begins the next cycle of the nearest enclosing "
"``for`` loop."
msgstr "``continue`` 陳述句會開始最近封閉 ``for`` 迴圈的下一個週期。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:29
msgid ""
"for i: uint256 in [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]:\n"
"    if i != a:\n"
"        continue\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""
"for i: uint256 in [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]:\n"
"    if i != a:\n"
"        continue\n"
"    ..."

#: ../../../statements.rst:36
msgid ""
"In the above example, the ``for`` loop begins the next cycle immediately "
"whenever ``i != a``."
msgstr "在上面的範例中，每當 ``i != a`` 時，``for`` 迴圈會立即開始下一個週期。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:39
msgid "pass"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../statements.rst:41
msgid ""
"``pass`` is a null operation — when it is executed, nothing happens. It is "
"useful as a placeholder when a statement is required syntactically, but no "
"code needs to be executed:"
msgstr ""
"``pass`` 是一個空操作——當它被執行時，什麼都不會發生。當語法上需要一個陳述句但"
"不需要執行任何程式碼時，它可用作佔位符："

#: ../../../statements.rst:43
msgid ""
"# this function does nothing (yet!)\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"def foo():\n"
"    pass"
msgstr ""
"# 此函數不做任何事（目前為止！）\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"def foo():\n"
"    pass"

#: ../../../statements.rst:52
msgid "return"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../statements.rst:54
msgid ""
"``return`` leaves the current function call with the expression list (or "
"None) as a return value."
msgstr "``return`` 會以運算式列表（或 None）作為傳回值離開目前的函數呼叫。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:56
msgid "return RETURN_VALUE"
msgstr "return RETURN_VALUE"

#: ../../../statements.rst:60
msgid ""
"If a function has no return type, it is allowed to omit the ``return`` "
"statement, otherwise, the function must end with a ``return`` statement, or "
"another terminating action such as ``raise``."
msgstr ""
"如果函數沒有傳回型別，則允許省略 ``return`` 陳述句，否則函數必須以 "
"``return`` 陳述句或其他終止動作（如 ``raise``）結尾。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:62
msgid ""
"It is not allowed to have additional, unreachable statements after a "
"``return`` statement."
msgstr "不允許在 ``return`` 陳述句之後有其他無法到達的陳述句。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:65
msgid "Event Logging"
msgstr "事件日誌紀錄"

#: ../../../statements.rst:68
msgid "log"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../statements.rst:70
msgid "The ``log`` statement is used to log an event:"
msgstr "``log`` 陳述句用於記錄事件："

#: ../../../statements.rst:72
msgid "log MyEvent(...)"
msgstr "log MyEvent(...)"

#: ../../../statements.rst:76
msgid "The event must have been previously declared."
msgstr "事件必須先前已宣告。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:78
msgid "See :ref:`Event Logging<event-logging>` for more information on events."
msgstr "更多事件資訊請參閱 :ref:`事件日誌紀錄<event-logging>`。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:81
msgid ""
"The evaluation order of arguments passed to ``log`` is undefined. The "
"compiler may evaluate them in any order. Therefore, arguments with side "
"effects should be evaluated in separate statements before the ``log`` call "
"to ensure predictable behavior."
msgstr ""
"傳遞給 ``log`` 的引數的求值順序是未定義的。編譯器可能以任意順序對它們進行求"
"值。因此，具有副作用的引數應在 ``log`` 呼叫之前以單獨的陳述句進行求值，以確保"
"行為可預測。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:84
msgid "Assertions and Exceptions"
msgstr "斷言與例外"

#: ../../../statements.rst:86
msgid ""
"Vyper uses state-reverting exceptions to handle errors. Exceptions trigger "
"the ``REVERT`` opcode (``0xFD``) with the provided reason given as the error "
"message. When an exception is raised the code stops operation, the "
"contract's state is reverted to the state before the transaction took place "
"and the remaining gas is returned to the transaction's sender. When an "
"exception happens in a sub-call, it \"bubbles up\" (i.e., exceptions are "
"rethrown) automatically."
msgstr ""
"Vyper 使用狀態還原例外來處理錯誤。例外會觸發 ``REVERT`` opcode（``0xFD``），"
"並以提供的原因作為錯誤訊息。當例外被引發時，程式碼停止操作，合約狀態還原到交"
"易發生前的狀態，剩餘的 gas 會退還給交易的發送者。當例外發生在子呼叫中時，它會"
"自動「向上氣泡化」（即例外會被重新拋出）。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:88
msgid ""
"If the reason string is set to ``UNREACHABLE``, an ``INVALID`` opcode "
"(``0xFE``) is used instead of ``REVERT``. In this case, calls that revert do "
"not receive a gas refund. This is not a recommended practice for general "
"usage, but is available for interoperability with various tools that use the "
"``INVALID`` opcode to perform dynamic analysis."
msgstr ""
"如果原因字串設為 ``UNREACHABLE``，則會使用 ``INVALID`` opcode（``0xFE``）而"
"非 ``REVERT``。在這種情況下，還原的呼叫不會收到 gas 退款。這不是一般用途的建"
"議做法，但可用於與使用 ``INVALID`` opcode 進行動態分析的各種工具之間的互通"
"性。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:91
msgid "raise"
msgstr "raise"

#: ../../../statements.rst:93
msgid ""
"The ``raise`` statement triggers an exception and reverts the current call."
msgstr "``raise`` 陳述句會觸發例外並撤銷當前呼叫。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:95
msgid "raise \"something went wrong\""
msgstr "raise \"something went wrong\""

#: ../../../statements.rst:99 ../../../statements.rst:123
msgid ""
"The error string is not required. If it is provided, it is limited to 1024 "
"bytes."
msgstr "錯誤字串並非必需。如果提供，則長度限制為 1024 位元組。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:101
msgid ""
"Custom errors can also be raised. They are declared at module scope and are "
"encoded with a 4-byte selector followed by ABI-encoded arguments:"
msgstr ""
"也可以引發自訂錯誤。它們在模組範圍中宣告，並以 4 位元組選擇器後跟 ABI 編碼的"
"引數進行編碼："

#: ../../../statements.rst:103
msgid ""
"error Unauthorized:\n"
"    caller: address\n"
"    expected: address\n"
"\n"
"raise Unauthorized(caller=msg.sender, expected=owner)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../statements.rst:111
msgid ""
"Custom errors are included in the generated ABI with ``type: \"error\"``."
msgstr "自訂錯誤包含在生成的 ABI 中，具有 ``type: \"error\"``。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:114
msgid "assert"
msgstr "assert"

#: ../../../statements.rst:117
msgid ""
"The ``assert`` statement makes an assertion about a given condition. If the "
"condition evaluates falsely, the transaction is reverted."
msgstr ""
"``assert`` 陳述句對給定條件進行斷言。如果條件求值為假，則交易會被還原。"

#: ../../../statements.rst:119
msgid "assert x > 5, \"value too low\""
msgstr "assert x > 5, \"value too low\""

#: ../../../statements.rst:125
msgid "This method's behavior is equivalent to:"
msgstr "此方法的行為等同於："

#: ../../../statements.rst:127
msgid ""
"if not cond:\n"
"    raise \"reason\""
msgstr ""
"if not cond:\n"
"    raise \"reason\""
